<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-424] Suggestion: Preparing to Install the Lustre Software section</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-424</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current online HTML manual provides detailed information of the packages should be installed to servers and clients.&#160; However, the current text seems to read &quot;The required packages for Lustre 2.9 EL7 servers are listed in the table below...&quot;.&#160; Rather than having the manual attempt to capture this dynamic information for one release, perhaps the details of a specific release could be removed, and in place there could instead be a hyperlink to the Wiki (perhaps to the &quot;Lustre Releases&quot; page at: &lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/PUB/Lustre+Releases&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/PUB/Lustre+Releases&lt;/a&gt;&#160;) where there is room to include the information for all the unique Lustre releases in a static context.&#160; Just a thought...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
